main event: Two unidentified objects were sighted in Collierville, Tennessee on 1-2 November 1966.
interesting points: The objects were observed for 15 minutes, with the witness reporting they appeared to be a permanent brilliant white color with a flashing blinking light at intervals.
The objects moved in a varied course and simply disappeared at one point while being watched.
The witness estimated the objects were traveling at around 50 mph and were approximately 1-1.5 miles away.
The witness reported seeing the objects while outdoors in the countryside, and they were observed through eyeglasses and the windshield of a vehicle.
Multiple people, described as a family of 4 or 5, also witnessed the objects.
